veryone loves pink and its a fun festival look</i>\\n  </p>\\n<p><b><i>Sophie Turner, Wella Professionals Global Brand Ambassador</i></b>   </p>\\n<p>\\n  </p>\\n<p>A true creative, semi-permanent* colour cream which fades true to tone over time and pastelizes during each wash, Wella Professionals Color Fresh CREATE, gradually fades into beautiful soft pastel hues and lasts up to 20 washes*, thanks to the carefully selected dyes that avoid an off tone fade, allowing clients to enjoy full creativity and freedom to change! Its Precision Cream formula enables controlled application and unlimited colouring techniques, while it is ammonia-free, fragrance-free and peroxide-free. Make your clients feel as unique as your creation with the new Color Fresh CREATE by Wella Professionals new semi-permanent expressive colour palette.\\n</p>\", \"e7d8d3ad-81d4-4164-b482-db5f8b283dcb\": false}',1,'2025-08-01 09:46:39','2025-08-01 09:46:45','b52cbbba-3a25-4eb4-8728-7c2322c117ff'),(1825,1825,1,'INTRODUCING OUR NEW SERVICE \"WELLA COLOUR FRESH CREATE\"','introducing-our-new-service-wella-colour-fresh-create','introducing-our-new-service-wella-colour-fresh-create','{\"89d6e74c-311b-4e96-a7f3-56d502e0cc13\": \"<p>The 1970s was a truly transformative decade, not only for its influence on fashion but as it also spawned a care-free attitude to experimentation that extended from lifestyle to hair color. The trend for bold, bright hair took hold with provocateurs from the 70s during the punk period, who created a legacy that lasted  and has grown  through the decades. After all, creativity thrives where colour lives  we see colour in every creative sphere, from designers catwalk creations to celebrity transformations on camera. Expressive colour is here and ready to go mainstream.\\n  </p>\\n<p>A few decades later the hair care colour space is experiencing a boom with the return of bold and pastel palettes. Cotys Wella Professionals introduces new Colour Fresh CREATE, ex expressive semi-per