side.gov.uk/Newsroom/Looking-forward-to-eating-out-or-getting-your-hair\\\">https://www.tameside.gov.uk/Ne...</a></p>\", \"e7d8d3ad-81d4-4164-b482-db5f8b283dcb\": false}',1,'2025-08-01 09:46:48','2025-08-01 09:46:48','40b4ecf7-d274-4974-a1c3-1ed522dad397'),(2050,2050,1,'Visit guidelines to prepare you for your covid safe visit to our salon','visit-guidelines-to-prepare-you-for-your-covid-safe-visit-to-our-salon','visit-guidelines-to-prepare-you-for-your-covid-safe-visit-to-our-salon','{\"89d6e74c-311b-4e96-a7f3-56d502e0cc13\": \"<p>In light of the current COVID-19 pandemic, we wanted to give you an update on the changes we are making in the salon to ensure your safety is our main priority.<br /></p>\\n<p>We are closely monitoring the government and industry advice, and have made some changes in how we operate under their best guidance.</p>\\n<p><strong>We have introduced a \\\"Covid19 surcharge of 2 for each client to cover our additional costs of making the salon environment a safe place for clients and staff alike whilst providing a PERSONALISED PACK that will contain a Face Mask, towel, disposable gown and cape.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>Guidelines mean there will be no dry cuts available during this Covid19 period.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>Arrive for your appointment 5 mins early and wait in your car or in a safe place and call the salon on 0161-368-9999 to let us know you have arrived and we will inform you when to come to the salon doors.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>Ring the bell upon arrival and you will be met by the receptionist.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>No need to wear a face mask as one will be provided to you in your pack.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>Please try to attend without LARGE bags and coats.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>Attend your appointment on your own.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>Staff &amp; clients will have their temperature checked before entering the salon.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>We are taking extra care to ensure we are sanitising and cleaning between each client in the chairs.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>We have introduced sanitation-stations with hand sanitiser  please use these, as much and as often as you can.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>The toilet facilities will remain available upon request to your stylist.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>We are still committed to your comfort while at The Leading Edge however you will notice we have begun serving our refreshments teas &amp; coffees in disposable cups and we promise we are doing our best to recycle and dispose of these ethically.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>You may also notice that we have removed magazines, again, this is to reduce germ transfer. Please feel free to bring in your own reading materials.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>All our salon stations adhere to the 2 metre social distancing guidelines and movement around the salon is restricted.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>Our team are following government recommendations and will all be isolating if they show flu-like symptoms, so we ask for your patience and understanding if we need to reschedule your appointment.</strong></p>\\n<p><strong>If you are unwell, or have come into contact with someone with COVID-19 in the last 14 days, please reschedule your appointment, even if you do not have any symptoms.</strong></p>\", \"e7d8d3ad-81d4-4164-b482-db5f8b283dcb\": false}',1,'2025-08-01 09:46:48','2025-08-01 09:46:53','00f61196-7484-49cd-a285-64409b3ffc0c'),(2051,2051,1,'Visit guidelines to prepare you for your covid safe visit to our salon','visit-guidelines-to-prepare-you-for-your-covid-safe-visit-to-our-salon','visit-guidelines-to-prepare-you-for-your-covid-safe-visit-to-our-salon','{\"89d6e74c-311b-4e96-a7f3-56d502e0cc13\": \"<p>In light of the current COVID-19 pandemic, we wanted to give you an update on the changes we are making in the salon to ensure your safety is our main priority.<br /></p>\\n<p>We are closely monitoring the government and industry advice, and have made some changes in how we operate 